				<div></div><p>Msakr,</p><p>I understand your caveots, and thanks for reiterating them.  I'm aware I cannot take your numbers directly for everything, but for the most part, they will serve as a starting point.</p><p>I plan to put together a calculator that will answer two basic questions:</p><ol><li>Given an expected success rate, a given sale price, and a given profit margin, what should I be willing to pay for raw materials?</li><li>Given an expected success rate, a given profit margin, and the price of raw materials, what is a good sale price for my product?</li></ol><p>Actually, thinking about it more, it is really an problem with four parameters.  Given any three of the parameters, I should be able to calculate the fourth.  I'll work on it and let you know how it comes out.</p><p> </p>
				
